  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tackling the drivers of sexual violence against girls in school  (South Africa)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In South Africa, girls from all levels of society are affected by sexual violence at school. This project develops and tests a range of approaches to reduce the occurrence of sexual violence in school. Activities include the creation of safer and more effective schools, safer homes and community environments, and strengthening the income of girls, women and their families so that girls are able to continue their education without having to engage in transactional sexual relations to cover the cost of education and that families don&#x2019;t feel compelled to remove daughters from school for financial reasons.</narrative>
  </description>
